# @file .env.example
# @description Mini README: Baseline environment variables for the Fusion Futures web app. Copy to `.env.local`
#   when developing locally so configuration stays out of version control.
#
# Structure
# ---------
# PORT       -> HTTP port for Next.js dev/prod servers. Mirrors CLI `--port` flag.
# FF_DEBUG   -> When "true", enables verbose logging and helper banners to aid debugging.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_NAME -> Shown in the browser UI so end users always know which environment they are using.
#
# Usage
# -----
# 1. Copy this file to `.env.local`.
# 2. Adjust values as needed (e.g., change ports to avoid clashes).
# 3. Restart the dev server after edits so Next.js reloads the variables.

PORT=3000
FF_DEBUG=false
NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_NAME=Fusion Futures (Local)
